OL,3,CCould 75,000 train ticket fines be
OL,4,Coverturned in landmark case?
OL,6,FA West Yorkshire man, who challenged a
OL,7,Ffine he received for travelling on a
OL,8,Ftrain without a ticket, may have
OL,9,Fopened the door for 75,000 other
OL,10,Fsimilar penalties to be overturned.
OL,12,FChristian Waters was unable buy a
OL,13,Fticket at his local station Kirkstall
OL,14,FForge when he was travelling to Leeds
OL,15,Fin 2022 because the machine was broken
OL,16,Fat the time.
OL,18,FHe received a penalty fare from
OL,19,FNorthern and ended up being taken to
OL,20,Fcourt for a criminal case over fare
OL,21,Fevasion.
