OL,3,CCould 75,000 train ticket fines be
OL,4,Coverturned in landmark case?
OL,6,FChristian challenged the use of an SJP
OL,7,Fand the case was taken up by the UK's
OL,8,FChief Magistrate Paul Goldspring.
OL,10,FIf he decides the use of SJPs in cases
OL,11,Fsuch as Christian's is unlawful, it
OL,12,Fwould mean 75,000 similar cases could
OL,13,Fbe quashed.
OL,15,FThose cases include prosecutions
OL,16,Fbrought by other train companies as
OL,17,Fwell as Northern.
OL,19,FChristian's case has led rail
OL,20,Fcampaigners to demand more discretion
OL,21,Ffor those who can't buy a ticket.
