OL,3,CCould 75,000 train ticket fines be
OL,4,Coverturned in landmark case?
OL,6,FNina Smith from Railfuture Yorkshire
OL,7,Fsaid: "It does seem wrong to me that
OL,8,Fyou can prosecute somebody in a closed
OL,9,Fcourt. If you're going to prosecute it
OL,10,Fshould be in an open court.
OL,12,F"Most people who are caught without a
OL,13,Fticket will pay a penalty notice and
OL,14,Fthat will be be it but it can be very
OL,15,Fdifficult sometimes to buy a ticket."
OL,17,FThe Chief Magistrate will make a
OL,18,Fdecision on 19th July.
